==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|know}} + {{term|it}} + {{term|all}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[know]]-[[it]]-[[all]]}

# One who acts as if he or she knows everything by pontificating and behaving as if they're above others.
#: ''We were all proposing ideas to solve the problem until some '''know-it-all''' strutted in the room claiming that none of our ideas would work and what would.''

